channel.title: Problem
channel.description:
I need help with fixing my No-Ip thing, finally with the help of I Am Noob, I got some of it to work.
My port is 43594 and my ip is correct (when I type it in). It works for me, but when other people try it, it doesn't work. Anyone know why? My firewalls are all down too.
I don't know but this might explain something to some of you.
I used Ultimate Pk scape as my source to build the server, and it ran on a 5555 port, so I had to chage it to 43594 by going into server.java do any of you all know if thats all I have to really do?
I used DnsDyn or something like that to create my domain, and then I logged into that at my routers setting.
**If you want me to post pictures of any of my settings just ask, Ill post em**
Help please! (If you play real RuneScape, I only have like 500k on my account and its almost out of member ship, but Ill give you 500k if you can help my fix my problem, I also have MSN and AIM. ) [br][size=1]Posted on: March 03, 2007, 03:13:06 PM[/size][hr]Add me: vraj821@hotmail.com

item.title: Problem
item.dc:creator: @liamsford liamsford
item.description:
@liamsford wrote:

[center] Put your FireWall UP.

Then open a port with your full server name ( Example=Spacescape.servegame.com ) and port 43594

Then open another port with your full server name ( example=Spacescape.servegame.com ) and port 5555 also.

So there is a port 5555 and 43594 open.

Also compile the server before you run it.

You can pay me if you want ;).
